  <!-- YOUR LINK -->
  <div class="faq-section" id="your-link">
    <p class="faq-section-tag">Getting started</p>
    <h2 class="faq-section-title">Your shareable link</h2>

    <div class="faq-item open">
      <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is my Ask link?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Your Ask link is a permanent public page that hosts your AI assistant. Anyone who visits it can ask questions about your professional background and get instant answers — even when you're not available. It looks like: <strong>ask.menoslabs.com/davidobrien-001</strong></div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Where should I share my Ask link?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">The best places are:
        <br><br>• <strong>Email signature</strong> — add "Ask me anything: [your link]" at the bottom of every email
        <br>• <strong>LinkedIn profile</strong> — add it to your About section or as a featured link
        <br>• <strong>Resume</strong> — include it next to your contact details
        <br>• <strong>Portfolio site</strong> — embed the chat button or link directly
        <br>• <strong>Job applications</strong> — include it in cover letters so recruiters can learn more
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Will my link ever expire?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">No. Your Ask link is permanent. You paid once and it lives forever at your URL. We don't delete profiles or charge recurring fees.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CUSTOM DOMAIN -->
  <div class="faq-section" id="custom-domain">
    <p class="faq-section-tag">Advanced setup</p>
    <h2 class="faq-section-title">Point to your own domain</h2>

    <div class="faq-item open">
      <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I use my own domain like ask.mysite.com?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Yes — you can point a subdomain of your own domain to your Ask profile. You'll need access to your domain's DNS settings. Here's how:
        <br><br>Add a CNAME record in your DNS settings:
        <div class="code-block">Type: CNAME
Name: ask (or any subdomain you want)
Value: ask.menoslabs.com</div>
        Then email us at <strong>hello@menoslabs.com</strong> with your domain and Ask URL and we'll configure the redirect.
        <div class="tip"><strong>Note:</strong> DNS changes can take up to 48 hours to propagate globally.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Which DNS providers does this work with?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">It works with any DNS provider — Cloudflare, GoDaddy, Namecheap, Google Domains, Route 53, and others. The CNAME record process is the same on all of them.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- EMBED -->
  <div class="faq-section" id="embed">
    <p class="faq-section-tag">Adding to your website</p>
    <h2 class="faq-section-title">Embed on your site</h2>

    <div class="faq-item open">
      <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How do I add the chat button to my website?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">
        Add one line of code to your website and a floating "Ask Me" button will appear in the bottom right corner.
        <div class="code-block" id="embedChatCode">&lt;script src="https://ask.menoslabs.com/embed.js" data-slug="YOUR-SLUG"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</div>
        <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode('embedChatCode',this)">Copy Code</button>
        <br><br>Replace <strong>YOUR-SLUG</strong> with your profile slug (the part after ask.menoslabs.com/ in your URL).

        <br><br>
        <div class="platform-tabs">
          <button class="ptab on" onclick="switchPlatform('wix',this)">Wix</button>
          <button class="ptab" onclick="switchPlatform('squarespace',this)">Squarespace</button>
          <button class="ptab" onclick="switchPlatform('wordpress',this)">WordPress</button>
          <button class="ptab" onclick="switchPlatform('other',this)">Any Site</button>
        </div>

        <div class="platform-panel on" id="platform-wix">
          <div class="steps">
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-text">In your Wix editor, click <strong>Add Elements</strong> in the left sidebar</div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-text">Select <strong>Embed Code</strong> → <strong>HTML iframe</strong></div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-text">Paste the script tag above into the HTML box</div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">4</div><div class="step-text">Click <strong>Apply</strong> — the chat button will appear on your live site</div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">5</div><div class="step-text">Publish your site</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="platform-panel" id="platform-squarespace">
          <div class="steps">
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-text">Go to the page where you want the chat button</div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-text">Click <strong>Edit</strong> → hover over a section → click <strong>+</strong></div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-text">Select a <strong>Code</strong> block</div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">4</div><div class="step-text">Paste the script tag above and click <strong>Apply</strong></div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">5</div><div class="step-text">Save and publish your page</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="platform-panel" id="platform-wordpress">
          <div class="steps">
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-text">In WordPress, go to <strong>Appearance → Theme Editor</strong></div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-text">Open <strong>footer.php</strong></div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-text">Paste the script tag just before the closing <strong>&lt;/body&gt;</strong> tag</div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">4</div><div class="step-text">Click <strong>Update File</strong> — the button appears on every page of your site</div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> You can also use a plugin like "Insert Headers and Footers" to add the code without editing theme files.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="platform-panel" id="platform-other">
          <div class="steps">
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-text">Open your website's HTML file</div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-text">Paste the script tag just before the closing <strong>&lt;/body&gt;</strong> tag</div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-text">Save and upload — the chat button will appear on every page</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How do I embed my full profile page?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Use an iframe to embed your complete profile page including experience, skills, and chat:
        <div class="code-block" id="embedFullCode">&lt;iframe src="https://ask.menoslabs.com/YOUR-SLUG" width="100%" height="700" frameborder="0" style="border:none;border-radius:4px;"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</div>
        <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode('embedFullCode',this)">Copy Code</button>
        <br><br>Replace <strong>YOUR-SLUG</strong> with your profile slug.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CHAT VS FULL -->
  <div class="faq-section" id="chat-vs-full">
    <p class="faq-section-tag">Embed options</p>
    <h2 class="faq-section-title">Chat button vs full page</h2>

    <div class="faq-item open">
      <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Which embed option should I use?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">
        <strong>Chat button (recommended for most sites)</strong> — A floating button appears in the corner of your existing site. It blends in cleanly without disrupting your design. Best for portfolios, personal websites, and agency sites.
        <br><br>
        <strong>Full profile page (iframe)</strong> — Embeds your complete Ask profile including your bio, experience timeline, skills, and chat. Best if you want to dedicate a full section or page to your profile.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- EDITING -->
  <div class="faq-section" id="editing">
